 BLUE BOOK n. 1. Informal name for one of the three standard references on
the page-layout and graphics-control language PostScript; the others are
known as the GREEN BOOK and RED BOOK. 2. Any of the 1988 standards issues by
the CCIT 9th plenary assembly. They change color each review cycle (1984 was
RED BOOK, 1992 will be GREEN BOOK). These include, among other things, the
X.400 email spec and the Group 1 through 4 fax standards. see also RED BOOK,
GREEN BOOK, SILVER BOOK, PURPLE BOOK, ORANGE BOOK, WHITE BOOK, PINK-SHIRT
BOOK, DRAGON BOOK.